10 new things that I learned from St. La Salle

1) his Full name is Jean-Baptiste de La Salle

2) His fiest day is on April 7

3) He had a lot of siblings

4) He died on Good Friday

5) He was the Patron Saint of Teachers

6) He dedicated much of his life for the education of poor children in France.

7) Declared a saint at May 29, 1900

8)The first son of a very wealthy familyin France.

9) He received the tonsure at age eleven.

10) He became involved in education "little by little".


